	                        <div class="columnOpen">
		                        <p class="columnOpenTitle">Middle Back Procedures</p>
		                        <p class="columnOpenPara" >The thoracic spine- or middle back- is responsible for movement of the torso. It is also a passageway for some important nerves that affect balance and leg function. The most common conditions in this region of the spine include disc degeneration and stenosis. Spinal tumors may also affect this region. Any of these conditions can cause mid back pain, flank pain, bowel or bladder conditions, or difficulty with balance and walking. Fortunately, many of problems are treated successfully with minimally invasive techniques.</p>
	                        </div><!-- columnOpen -->
	                        
